ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Overall, has this pregnancy been a positive experience for you?
Do you feel you will have people you can depend on for emotional support when you go home with your baby?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 3= Somewhat; 5= Very Much

ElementDescription: When you were growing up, do you think your mother was happy to be a mother?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 3= Somewhat; 5= Very Much

ElementDescription: When you were growing up, did you feel that your mother was critical of you?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 3= Somewhat; 6= Very Much

ElementDescription: When you were growing up, did you feel your mother was emotionally supportive of you?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 3= Somewhat; 6= Very Much

ElementDescription: At present, is your mother emotionally supportive? (circle 6 if mother not alive)
Notes: 1= Not at all; 3= Somewhat; 6= Very Much

ElementDescription: When you were growing up, did you feel that your father as critical of you?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 3= Somewhat; 6= Very Much

ElementDescription: When you were growing up, did you feel your father was emotionally supportive?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 3= Somewhat; 6= Very Much

ElementDescription: Before this pregnancy did you ever have a period of 2 weeks or more when you felt particularly miserable or depressed?
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: If you did have a period of 2 weeks or more when you felt particularly miserable or depressed, did it interfere with your ability to get things done or your relationships with your friends and family?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 3= Somewhat; 5= Very Much

ElementDescription: If you did have a period of 2 weeks or more when you felt particularly miserable or depressed, did it lead you to seek professional help?
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: Have you ever been told by a health professional you were depressed or needed antidepressants?
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: During this pregnancy have you been distressed by feelings of anxiety or depression for 2 weeks or more?
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: If you have been distressed by feelings of anxiety or depression for 2 weeks or more, did this lead you to seek professional help?
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: If you have been distressed by feelings of anxiety or depression for 2 weeks or more, did this interfere with your ability to get things done or your relationships with friends and family?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 3= Somewhat; 5= Very Much

ElementDescription: Is your relationship with your partner an emotionally supportive one? (If you have no partner circle 6)
Notes: 1= Not at all; 3= Somewhat; 6= Very Much

ElementDescription: Have you had any major stresses, changes or losses in the course of this pregnancy (e.g. separation, moving house, domestic violence, bereavement)?
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: To what extent has this stress a?ected your emotional well being?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 3= Somewhat; 5= Very Much

ElementDescription: Would you generally consider yourself a worrier?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 3= Somewhat; 5= Very Much

ElementDescription: In general, are you the sort of person who has trouble ?nishing jobs because you want to get it exactly right?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 3= Somewhat; 5= Very Much

ElementDescription: Do you generally like yourself as a person?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 3= Somewhat; 5= Very Much

ElementDescription: Before age 16, were you ever abused or physically attacked (not sexually) by someone you knew (for example, a parent, boyfriend, or husband, hit, slapped, choked, burned, or beat you up?
Notes: 0=No; 1=Yes

ElementDescription: How many children do you have (including stepchildren or adopted children)?
Notes: 1 = None; 2 = 1; 3 = 2; 4 = 3 or more

ElementDescription: How many of these children live with you?
Notes: 1 = None; 2 = 1; 3 = 2; 4 = 3 or more

ElementDescription: During the past 3 months, have you tried to become pregnant?
Notes: 0=No; 1=Yes

ElementDescription: During the past 3 months, have you been pregnant?
Notes: 0=No; 1=Yes

ElementDescription: During the past 3 months, have you been on a form of birth control or contraceptive (for example, birth control pill, patch, vaginal ring, shot, implant, IUD, or diaphram)? Do not count condom use in your answer.
Notes: 0=No; 1=Yes

ElementDescription: Thinking about your life right now, how important is it to you to avoid becoming pregnant?
Notes: 0 = Not at all important; 1 = A little important; 2 = Somewhat important; 3 = Very important

ElementDescription: If you found out today that you were pregnant, would you feel...
Notes: 1 = Very upset; 2 = A little upset; 3 = A little pleased; 4 = Very pleased

ElementDescription: Thinking about your life right now, how important is it to you to avoid getting a woman pregnant?
Notes: 0 = Not at all important; 1 = A little important; 2 = Somewhat important; 3 = Very important

ElementDescription: If you found out today that you got a woman pregnant, would you feel...
Notes: 1 = Very upset; 2 = A little upset; 3 = A little pleased; 4 = Very pleased
